    },
    {
      question: "Why start at £2,000 when I've been quoted a few hundred?",
      answer:
        "Because a £300 website and a £2,000 website aren't the same product at different prices — they're different things. The cheap one is usually a template filled in fast, with no thought to whether it ranks or turns visitors into enquiries. Mine are designed around getting you work and built to last.",
    },
    {
      question: "How long does it take?",
      answer:
        "Most builds run a few weeks from our first call to launch — the variable is usually how quickly content and photos come together, not the build itself. I'll give you an honest timeline up front.",
    },
    {
      question: "Will I be able to update it myself?",
      answer:
        "Yes. I hand-build on WordPress partly so you're never held hostage for a simple text change. You get a training video and a site you can actually edit — swap images, change copy, add a page. I'm there when you want me, not because you're stuck.",
    },
    {
      question: "Do I need to be in York?",
      answer:
        "No. I'm based in Skipton and work with businesses across York, North Yorkshire and the wider county. Plenty of the work happens remotely via video calls. Where you are matters far less than whether we're a good fit.",
    },
    {
      question: "What about hosting and domains?",
      answer:
        "I handle both. Your domain is registered in your name — you own it. Hosting is fast, secure, and managed. Everything is yours to take with you if you ever want to leave. No lock-in, no hostage fees.",
    },
